24/03/2011
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- President Danilo Turk and visiting Croatian counterpart Ivo Josipovic agreed on Wednesday (March 23rd) that relations between their countries are continually improving.
They said that Croatia's EU accession will be in the interest not only of Zagreb and Ljubljana, but all of Europe.
No other details of the talks were revealed.
The two are expected to meet again next month.
(Radio Free Europe, Hina, tportal.hr - 23/03/11)
